{
  "abstract": "Recent years have witnessed remarkable growth\r\nin private sector investment in crop improvement,\r\nresearch and development, especially in crops\r\nthat provide hybrid cultivar options. The sorghum\r\nand pearl millet hybrid seed industry has a wellestablished\r\nbase in India and has derived\r\nimmense economic benefits from hybrid parents\r\nresearch at ICRISAT. Pigeonpea hybrids are also\r\nnow becoming a commercially viable proposition.",
